Agnieszka & Karu,

In Eric's defense, I did try and call both of you on Friday arvo just =20=

to clarify what you meant by the new rules/policy and I couldn't get on =20=

to either of you.  Sending something out an email on a topic such as =20
the ICS PGRF on a  Friday afternoon afternoon is always going to look =20=

bad, especially when you are not there to clear up any misconceptions - =20=

such as the one I had.  Even if Friday afternoon is the first chance =20
you have, you may want to delay sending out such information until =20
Monday morning instead?

I agree that we should try and maximise our use of the MQ PGRF as this =20=

will maximise the money into the division, which is a great thing.  =20
However, I just hope that we are not moving in the direction of using =20=

the MQ PGRF for funding essential parts of our degree and moving away =20=

from the main aim of the MQ PGRF which is to "provide the University=92s =
=20
postgraduate research students with the means to enhance their =20
postgraduate research experience and add value to their thesis".

On a similar note, I have had no personal experience with any ICS PGRF =20=

applications being knocked back, although I haven't really written as =20=

many papers as I should have by now.  So, I would appreciate it if =20
anyone who has had an ICS PGRF application knocked back (current or =20
past application) because there wasn't enough money there for them to =20=

please contact me or one of the other reps with the details so that we =20=

can starting building up some data on this topic.  Matt, you sound like =20=

you have some information on this.  Without these details, we (the =20
reps) really can't do much.

Cheers
James



