</excerpt>Round 2, 2007 -- now open

<excerpt>


This message was sent by Macquarie University Research Office

and authorised by Prof. Jim Piper, Deputy Vice Chancellor (Research)


Round 2, 2007 of the PGRF Scheme is now open.  Funding Rules and

application material are available from the Research Office

website at

http://www.research.mq.edu.au/researchers/funding/internal/pgrf2


The closing date for receipt of hardcopy applications in the Research

Office is Friday 13 April 2007 at 5.00pm.  Electronic copies of

applications must also be received by the closing date, emailed to

grants@mq.edu.au.


Important points to note:


It is the applicant's responsibility to ensure that the Supervisor's

Report Form is submitted independently of the application by the

closing

date in both hardcopy and electronically to grants@mq.edu.au.

Applications for which no Supervisor's Report Form is received by the

closing date will be ruled ineligible.


Applicants should also be aware that Departmental and Divisional

sign-off can take several days and ensure adequate time is allowed

for

this processing.  Divisions should also ensure timely processes

are put

in place for signing applications so that they can be received in the

Research Office by the due date.  Processing of applications in

time for

interviews to take place is such that late applications cannot be

accepted and will be deferred until the next round of the scheme.


Any queries relating to this scheme should be directed to Ellen

Young,

ext 4462 or email Ellen.Young@vc.mq.edu.au





Ellen Young

Grants Officer

Research Office

Macquarie University




